Erichson
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="159" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1156,210,407]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">
The family 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1837" box="[295,433,210,234]" class="Insecta" family="Spercheidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Spercheidae</taxonomicName>
is a homogeneous group of beetles composed of only one genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kugelann. Recent" authorityName="Kugelann. Recent" box="[241,554,244,269]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Spercheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[241,350,244,269]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">Spercheus</emphasis>
Kugelann. Recent
</taxonomicName>
papers mention that this family has 18 species, most of them from the Ethiopian and 
<collectingRegion box="[528,617,279,303]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">Oriental</collectingRegion>
zoogeographic regions (
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen M" box="[898,1047,279,303]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" refId="ref4864" refString="Hansen M. 1991. The Hydrophiloid beetles. Phylogeny, classification and a revision of genera (Coleoptera: Hydrophiloidea). Copenhagen: The Royal Danish Academy of Sciences and Letters." type="book" year="1991">Hansen 1991</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hebauer F" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" pagination="9 - 42" refId="ref4964" refString="Hebauer F. 1997. Revision der arten der Familie Spercheidae Erichson, 1837 (Coleoptera, Hydrophiloidea). Entomol Bl Biol Syst Kaefer. 93: 9 - 42." type="journal article" year="1997">Hebauer 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Darilmaz MC &amp; Kiyak S" box="[229,510,313,338]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" pagination="441 - 444" refId="ref4765" refString="Darilmaz MC, Kiyak S. 2011. A study on the family Spercheidae (Coleoptera) from Turkey. Turk J Zool. 35: 441 - 444." type="journal article" year="2011">Darilmaz and KÄ±yak 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="159" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1156,210,407]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">
Until now, only a single Oriental subspecies, 
<taxonomicName authority="belli" box="[714,928,347,372]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Spercheus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="belli" subSpecies="belli">
<emphasis box="[714,928,347,372]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">Spercheus belli belli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has been recorded in 
<collectingCountry box="[190,283,383,407]" name="Pakistan" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hebauer F" box="[297,458,383,407]" pageId="10" pageNumber="159" pagination="9 - 42" refId="ref4964" refString="Hebauer F. 1997. Revision der arten der Familie Spercheidae Erichson, 1837 (Coleoptera, Hydrophiloidea). Entomol Bl Biol Syst Kaefer. 93: 9 - 42." type="journal article" year="1997">Hebauer 1997</bibRefCitation>
). The species is recorded here also for 
<collectingCountry box="[908,1004,383,407]" name="Pakistan" pageId="10" pageNumber="159">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
